DialogueLine.dialogue: G'morning, Ma'am.
What? How could that happen?
I have no idea where he is, sorry. You could ask one of the custodians or the assistant.
I think I saw a strange woman in the storage room last night. My memory was hazy so I assumed it was just one of the staff.
Uhm... no. I haven't done anything. Are you implying something?
What are you trying to say? If there's something you're implying you need evidence for it. Please leave me alone.
I don't think Cass is capable of that... She loves her career. I doubt she will jeopardize it.
I'm not sure who that woman is. Maybe she could be the woman I saw in the cameras.
Hmmm... the name doesn't ring any bells. But! I did forget to tell you, I think I saw a woman in the storage room cameras. Could that be 'Beth'?
Yes, I was watching the cameras throughout the night. I've been a bit sleep-deprived... but I know what I saw.
I'm sorry. I was watching the cameras throughout the night, and I've been a bit sleep-deprived... so I may have forgotten.
If you need to, you can call him through my phone.
Hey, have you called the director already?
H-hey, don't be too harsh on him, he's probably busy.
What, really? Hmm... I wonder what he's up to.
But I just saw you call someone. Please don't use the phone for unimportant matters.
Okay. Let me know if there's anything new.
...Huh. Usually, he lets his assistants know where he goes--n-not that I look for him often.
I'm not sure I can help... I guess Virgil--I mean, the director--leaves a spare key for his office here.
Oh. I can't. The director is a pretty private person. He wouldn't want me to give away the key randomly.
Ah, sure. I'll help you out. Just as long as you won't tell him I gave you the keys.
Oh... I... I can't. Sorry. The director trusted me with the key, and he's a very private person...
Just doing my job. You can't blame me for that.
I'm really sorry. I hope someone else helps though.
It's just a shot in the dark basically. But... I know 'Beth' isn't the director's wife.
Yes. And... well, it just seems to me that the director may attract people like this. Like... the Founder.
I've read that a lot of nautical artifacts have a lot of value. They're considered collector's items and deep sea treasures. The director... attracts people that want these artifacts for themselves.
Yes, the founder. She funded and helped build the museum. Rumors say she uses the museum as a way to collect some nautical artifacts. If she wants to collect it, she buys it from us.
I don't often think about her. But listen, I hear the director often does whatever the founder wants.
I... just hear about it. From other people. I'm sure if you gossip enough with everyone here, they have something to say about her.
Well... Maybe. I've never seen the founder before. It makes a lot of sense for the founder to be the one in the cameras too. And if she's also Beth, then she's our most likely culprit.
Here's the spare key to the director's office. I suppose this is an important matter, so take it.
What did you find?
I don't know. Maybe it could be the assistant's? Ask her.
Let me see that...Beth, huh? I'm not sure who that is. It's certainly not his wife though.
A lot of people drop by the museum, so I can't really pinpoint who always visits and who doesn't. The woman that Cassandra was talking about sounds familiar.
Oh, her! Yes, she could be Beth. She often brings us cookies and goes straight up to the second floor.
That's true...
Th-there wasn't? I'm sure there was. I knew I was wide awake then, and I know what I saw...
I wasn't lying! I know what I saw...
I'm not throwing her under the bus! Maybe I'm just... mistaken.
Oh... yes. I heard of it.
I'm not throwing her under the bus! Yes, I don't like her, but not enough to blame her for theft. I just think that the director shouldn't be blindly following her whims.
I'm not throwing her under the bus! I don't like her, but I'm not blaming her for no reason!

The truth is... the director is completely infatuated with her. His marriage... fell apart because he prioritized the founder over everything else. I know it's not the founder's fault... but I thought, if the founder went down, then Virgil would be back to normal.
Oh, yes. Why do you ask?
We... we go way back. I guess you could say the director helped me out plenty of times.
That's pretty rude. To answer your question, it's because he and I go way back.
If you're going to ask me things, you better be polite. I just made a mistake, is all.
Oh... no. Why?
It's none of your business.
Oh, it's nothing. It's mostly the slip of the tongue.
Oh, it's just that I got used to using his first name. Let's change the topic.
Yes, we do know each other. He's helped me through some tough times before.

Oh, yes. He has helped me a lot when we were younger, including hiring me for this job. He knows I like history, but since I didn't have any other qualifications, he just hired me to be a guard for now.
We don't.
...Yes. I wanted to protect him and his family.
...Yes. I wanted to protect him and his family. Did you know that he's been missing his daughter's birthdays for a while now? He's not the same man I once knew.

If I had to guess, it's because Ma'am Cassandra disagrees with how he deals with the Aurora artifacts. But that's about the extent of what I know. You'll have to ask someone else; maybe Ma'am Cass or {speakerArchetype:assistant}.
I'm not framing her! That's a heavy word to use. I just think that if the founder leaves Virgil alone, he'll go back to normal.
I guess I was hoping to end whatever relationship they may have. I don't think the founder likes him like that, but Virgil bends over backwards for her.
Yes, feel free to come back if you have more questions.
Wh-what?! Did you look at my calendar?! Mind your own business! I'm done talking.
...yes. Just for the record, you shouldn't look at people's personal items.
Yes, I've been struggling recently. That's all I can say about that.
No. Maybe the custodians know?
Yes... it's odd. I don't know how it got there, though.
No! I don't think the director is like that.
I don't know... I'm guessing it was dropped during one of their meetings.
I was in my booth over there. Although, there were times that I would visit Ma'am Cass throughout the night.
I visited her twice.
Yes, I did. She was walking out the bathroom with a pretty big gash. I helped her clean it up.
My first visit. That was about two hours after closing.
For my first visit, I just wanted to make small talk about whatever artifact she was researching. In my second visit, I wanted to ask her about the woman in the storage room.
Thanks for believing me, I guess.
That's because when I got to the curator's office, I couldn't find her.
I know, I was wrong about that. Either way, I wasn't able to tell her because she wasn't in the office.
When I left the curator's office, I found her by the vending machine, getting coffee.

For my first visit, I just wanted to make small talk about whatever artifact she was researching. In my second visit, I wanted to ask her about the woman in the storage room. I know I was mistaken, and that there was no woman, but at the time, I really wanted to make sure.
I'll talk to you later.
I'm not hiding *anything*. I just think... maybe... maybe I was wrong. I wasn't sure if I really saw a woman, so...

I'm not trying to throw the founder under the bus. It's just that I saw an unfamiliar woman in the cameras. And I know, there weren't any, but I saw what I saw. No one else but the founder and the staff could have known about the plinth.
I'm not trying to throw the founder under the bus. It's just that... given what I know about their relationship, it just feels likely for the person to take it to be the founder.
Oh, this is the statue?! That's mesmerizing...
I'm sorry to ask, but can I see it?! I've never seen the plinth, and this must be beautiful...
Interesting. And you say this came *from* the founder? I... didn't expect that.
H...hey, Enid. How was the vacation?
I guess so. But it's not really my place to talk about it. Why?
Sorry, I don't know much. Why?
I appreciate that you told me the truth, but geez. You should probably mind your own business once this is all over.
Well, thanks for telling the truth, but damn. You've changed a lot since your vacation. I didn't think you were this nosy.
Oh. I don't know much, sorry.
Well, when you put it that way... We were close, yes, but I don't really want to talk about his problems. All I can say is he's made a fair amount of mistakes with his family.
Miss Cassandra could be correct, but... I'm sorry, I don't know what the visitor looks like.
Garden beds? No, I didn't notice anything particularly suspicious.
Yes... It's not really your business anymore.
Thanks for doing this, even if it's not really your responsibility.
It's okay, you don't have to ask. And wait--you're saying there's no one suspicious on it? Because I could have sworn I saw a suspicious woman last night...
Right. Unfortunately, I don't know where the director is. Do you know who could have done it?
What? Is there a way for me to help?
No, but I happen to know someone who does. The custodians keep an extra in their locker.
Not really. Plus, it's not like I'd be able to tell you, considering my priority is security.
Oh, I'm sorry, I can't tell you that.
No, but... F-fine. The custodians keep an extra key in their locker. You should ask around for the passcode. I'm just helping you for our old friendship.
